.SH DESCRIPTION

Follow these rules in the order they are listed. Perform the first action that applies

.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step].
If the button is blue and the button says "Abort", hold the button and refer to 
.I Releasing a Held Button.
.IP \n+[step].
If there is more than 1 battery on the bomb and the button says "Detonate", press and immediately release the button.
.IP \n+[step].
If the button is white and there is a lit indicator with label CAR, hold the button and refer to
.I Releasing a Held Button.
.IP \n+[step].
If there are more than 2 batteries on the bomb and there is a lit indicator with label FRK, press and immediately release the button.
.IP \n+[step].
If the button is yellow, hold the button and refer to
.I Releasing a Held Button.
.IP \n+[step].
If the button is red and the button says "Hold", press and immediately release the button.
.IP \n+[step].
If none of the above apply, hold the button and refer to
.I Releasing a Held Button.

.SH Releasing a Held Button 
If you start holding the button down, a colored strip will light up on the right side of the module.
Based on its color you must release the button at a specific point in time:

\(bu Blue strip: release when the countdown timer has a 4 in any position.

\(bu White strip: release when the countdown timer has a 1 in any position.

\(bu Yellow strip: release when the countdown timer has a 5 in any position.

\(bu Any other color strip: release when the countdown timer has a 1 in any position.
